
How to get started with the GrowERP mobile backend?

execute the following script file to load standard Moqui and 
our specific component mobile backend.

1. Clone the Moqui.

	$ git clone https://github.com/moqui/moqui-framework.git moqui && cd moqui

2. Copy myaddons.xml from GrowERP-backend-mobile repository to the moqui dir.

	$ git archive --remote=ssh://awsadmin@www.antwebsystems.com:55555/GrowERP-backend-mobile.git HEAD myaddons.xml | tar -x

3. Get the "GrowERP-backend-mobile" component and its dependencies.

	$ ./gradlew getComponent -Pcomponent=GrowERP-backend-mobile

4. Build and Load seed data.

	$ ./gradlew build
	$ java -jar moqui.war load types=seed,seed-initial
	$ java -jar moqui.war

5. Go to the browser for local (URL : http:localhost:8080), 
it will show the screen to initial create admin user for the GrowERP mobile backejava -jar moqui.warnd.


runtime/mobile should be an external directory and not in the docker instance


the mobile frontends can be downloaded here iwth git hub: 
growerp branch ecommerce: https://github.com/growerp/growerp/ecommerce
growerp-mobile: https://github.com/growerp/growerp-backend-mobile
